title: 820-4924 - No Liquid Damage, No Boot, No Vcore
message:
Hey guys, 

I have this 820-4924, customer just brought it in saying it does not come on, 

Absolutely no liquid damage anywhere, I triple inspected it with microscope, then Just for fun I ultrasonic cleaned it, 

also reballed SMC, once that worked, still the same, no change, 

PPBUS_G3H - Present - 12.59V
PP3V42_G3H - Present - 3.42V
PP5V_S5 - Present - 5V
[LEFT][COLOR=#353535][FONT=Arial][SIZE=12px]PPVRTC_G3H - Present 3.42V[/SIZE][/FONT][/COLOR][/LEFT]
PPBUS S5 HS COMPUTING - Present - 12.6V - Should be 8.6V - so im guessing is high
[LEFT][COLOR=#353535][FONT=Arial][SIZE=12px]SMC_BC_ACOK - Present - 3.4V
SMC_PM_G2_EN - Present - 3.42V
SMC_ONOFF_L - Present - 3.42V[/SIZE][/FONT][/COLOR][/LEFT]


PPVCC_S0_CPU - Not Present
[LEFT][COLOR=#353535][FONT=Arial][SIZE=12px]PM_SLP_SUS_L - Not Present[/SIZE][/FONT][/COLOR][/LEFT]
[LEFT][COLOR=#353535][FONT=Arial][SIZE=12px]PM_BATLOW_L - Not Present[/SIZE][/FONT][/COLOR][/LEFT]
[LEFT][COLOR=#353535][FONT=Arial][SIZE=12px]PP3V3_S4 Not Present[/SIZE][/FONT][/COLOR][/LEFT]
[LEFT][COLOR=#353535][FONT=Arial][SIZE=12px]PP5V_S4 - Not Present[/SIZE][/FONT][/COLOR][/LEFT]
[LEFT][COLOR=#353535][FONT=Arial][SIZE=12px]PP3V3_S5 - Not Present[/SIZE][/FONT][/COLOR][/LEFT]
PP5V S4 Not Present
PP5V S3 Not Present
PP5V S0 Not Present


Please HELP!

title: 820-4924 - No Liquid Damage, No Boot, No Vcore
message: Any pulse at least at 5V_S4 rail?

title: 820-4924 - No Liquid Damage, No Boot, No Vcore
message: PP3v3_S5 is not present, so there is likely the problem. Check resistance to ground on that rail for a short. If it is ok, likely could be a bad TPS51980. If shorted, find the short!
